<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,310,514,540]" box="[189,310,514,540]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,514,540]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,514,540]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,561,763]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[369,551,561,587]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentifrons" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[369,551,561,587]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. argentifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[557,648,562,588]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
except following characteristics: postocellar spots larger than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[189,332,597,623]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentifrons" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,332,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">argentifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[338,428,597,623]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and almost joined at posteromedian part of vertex (
<figureCitation box="[1028,1117,596,623]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatrigon spp., head, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E–F. M.natalensissp. nov.(arrow =postocellarspot)(♁).G.M.sexmaculatus sp. nov.(♁).H. M.apiformis sp. nov. (♁). I. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). J. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). K. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). L. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). M. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀). Symbol: x = postocellar spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849882/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
); on face microtrichiose stripes along eye margin and median facial stripe very reduced, present only as a tiny line but on the whole length; setae on vertex more dense and intensively yellow, and on the frons also yellow, not silvery-white like in 
<taxonomicName authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[430,611,702,728]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentifrons" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[430,611,702,728]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. argentifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[617,707,703,729]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[721,808,702,729]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatrigon spp., head, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E–F. M.natalensissp. nov.(arrow =postocellarspot)(♁).G.M.sexmaculatus sp. nov.(♁).H. M.apiformis sp. nov. (♁). I. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). J. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). K. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). L. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). M. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀). Symbol: x = postocellar spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849882/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
); microtrichia on mesoscutum reduced to traces of lateral and submedian stripes (
<figureCitation box="[546,639,737,763]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[291,1281,1100,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[291,1281,1100,1931]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Megatrigon spp., mesoscutum, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). B. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). C. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). D. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849890/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,324,803,829]" box="[189,324,803,829]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,803,829]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,803,829]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,849,946]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
The species epithet, which is formed as a geographical genitive, is derived from the name of the province in 
<collectingCountry box="[223,379,884,910]" name="South Africa" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[395,582,884,910]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">KwaZulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
, from where the 
<typeStatus box="[797,848,885,911]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
series of this species originate, i.e., the 
<typeStatus box="[1348,1399,885,911]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
