<figureCitation box="[379,411,1380,1407]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[188,231,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Megatrigon spp., left antenna, lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849886/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">3E</figureCitation>
). Distance between eyes relatively large, 0.20–0.21 × width of head, larger than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[189,344,1416,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,344,1416,1441]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[352,485,1415,1442]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[664,849,1415,1442]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentifrons" status="sp. nov.">
M. 
<emphasis box="[706,849,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">argentifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[857,951,1416,1442]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; post-ocular orbit narrow, but slightly wider than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[350,503,1451,1476]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[350,503,1451,1476]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[510,641,1450,1477]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 0.10 × width of head; ocellar triangle eqilateral, without median longitudinal groove; postpedicel (
<figureCitation box="[587,675,1486,1512]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[188,231,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Megatrigon spp., left antenna, lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849886/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
) similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[814,968,1486,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[814,968,1486,1511]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[976,1109,1486,1512]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but pedicel is relatively short (postpedicel 2 × as long as pedicel).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1398,1586,1647]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
THORAX (
<figureCitation box="[295,386,1586,1613]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[291,1281,1100,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[291,1281,1100,1931]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Megatrigon spp., mesoscutum, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). B. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). C. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). D. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849890/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Microtrichia on mesoscutum reduced so that only traces remain of the submedian and lateral microtrichiose stripes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1398,1687,1749]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">WING. Almost entirely covered by microtrichia, only few microtrichia missing in cell br basally, and above vena spuria.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1056,1787,1814]" box="[189,1056,1787,1814]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">LEGS. Tarsi orange-brown, only tarsomere 1 of metaleg darkened dorsally.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,1853,1985]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
ABDOMEN (
<figureCitation box="[314,385,1853,1879]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Megatrigon spp., habitus, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849878/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figs 
<geoCoordinate box="[371,385,1853,1879]" degrees="1, 7" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" precision="5555" value="1.7">1</geoCoordinate>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[400,432,1853,1879]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1862,1888]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Megatrigon spp., abdomen, dorsal view, ♁. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849902/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">7E</figureCitation>
). Setae on tergites yellow-gold; abdomen more narrow (tergite 3 is 1.9 × as wide as long) than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[346,498,1889,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[346,498,1889,1914]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[506,638,1888,1915]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; silver spots on tergites 2+3 are 1.20–1.25 as long as wide; silver spots on tergite 3 partly covered with setae, especially near to median part of tergites (in 
<taxonomicName authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[1183,1359,1923,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentifrons" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1183,1359,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. argentifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
setae are very reduced); tergite 4 without microtrichiose spots. Male genitalia in 
<figureCitation box="[1165,1268,1958,1985]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1825,1851]" captionTargetBox="[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 10. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, epandrium, left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. Megatrigon sp. from sexfasciatus group. M. M. nivalis. Symbols: x = ventral margin of median surstyle; y = posterior surstyle; z = cercus; w = subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849914/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Figs 10E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1282,1328,1959,1985]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium (A–M) and phallus (N), left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. sp. from sexfasciatus group. M–N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = hamus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849918/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">11E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1341,1388,1959,1985]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,232,1794,1820]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 12. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium, ventral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. apiformis sp. nov. G. M. cooksoni sp. nov. H. M. immaculatus sp. nov. I. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. J. M. tabanoides sp. nov. K. Megatrigon sp. from the sexfasciatus group. L. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = lateral ‘shoulders’." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849922/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">12E</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
